# Vision Quality Rules

## Purpose

This file defines the quality standards, scoring dimensions, minimum thresholds, and readiness classification criteria for Vision Documents. These rules govern the Vision Quality Assessment Skill and the Vision Analyst Agent.

> **AI Instruction**: Apply these rules when evaluating any Vision Document. A Vision Document that fails minimum thresholds must not proceed to architecture generation. Direct the user to Prompt 00 for guided remediation.

---

## Scoring Model

### Rule VQ-001: Dimensions and Scale

Evaluate each dimension on a scale of 1–5 using the criteria below. Do not average; every dimension must meet its minimum individually.

| Dimension | ID | Weight | Minimum Required |
|---|---|---|---|
| Problem Statement | VQ-D01 | Standard | 3 |
| Ideal Future | VQ-D02 | Standard | 2 |
| Actors and Users | VQ-D03 | Critical | 3 |
| Interface Preferences | VQ-D04 | Critical | 3 |
| Key Capabilities | VQ-D05 | Critical | 3 |
| Information and Concepts | VQ-D06 | Standard | 2 |
| Workflows and Journeys | VQ-D07 | Critical | 3 |
| Quality Priorities | VQ-D08 | Standard | 2 |
| Constraints and Non-Goals | VQ-D09 | Standard | 2 |
| Success Metrics | VQ-D10 | Standard | 2 |
| System Components Vision | VQ-D11 | Conditional | N/A |

**Total possible score**: 55 points (11 dimensions × 5)

**Critical dimensions** (VQ-D03, VQ-D04, VQ-D05, VQ-D07): a score below 3 on any critical dimension classifies the document as Insufficient regardless of total score.

### Rule VQ-002: Readiness Classification

| Classification | Total Score | Critical Dimension Condition | Meaning |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Ready** | 38–55 | All critical ≥ 3 | Architecture generation can proceed |
| **Needs Improvement** | 28–37 | All critical ≥ 3 | Architecture generation is possible but output quality will be degraded; refinement strongly recommended |
| **Insufficient** | < 28 | OR any critical < 3 | Architecture generation must not proceed; Prompt 00 required |

> **AI Instruction**: If the document is Insufficient, halt and direct the user to Prompt 00. If it is Needs Improvement, warn the user about the specific gaps and offer to continue or refine first. Never proceed silently with an Insufficient document.

---

## Scoring Criteria per Dimension

### Rule VQ-D01: Problem Statement

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | Current situation described with specific examples or data; clearly identifies who is affected; quantifies cost or consequence of inaction; includes description of current solutions and their shortcomings |
| 4 | Describes situation concretely; identifies affected parties; references current solutions; may lack quantification |
| 3 | Problem described but vague; affected parties mentioned; limited or no mention of current approaches |
| 2 | Only a partial description; problem is implied rather than stated; no stakeholders identified |
| 1 | Problem not described or is one sentence with no context |

### Rule VQ-D02: Ideal Future

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | Vivid description of the desired end state; explains what becomes possible; uses concrete outcomes rather than feature lists |
| 4 | Clear description of desired state; references concrete outcomes |
| 3 | General vision present but vague or focused on features rather than outcomes |
| 2 | Brief or aspirational statement with no concrete outcomes |
| 1 | Missing or one sentence |

### Rule VQ-D03: Actors and Users (Critical)

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | 3+ actors defined; each has role, primary need, frequency, and technical level; narrative context provided for at least one; external systems identified if applicable |
| 4 | 3+ actors defined with most fields filled; minor gaps in some actors |
| 3 | At least 2 actors defined with role, need, and frequency; technical level may be missing |
| 2 | 1–2 actors with incomplete information; generic descriptions ("the user") |
| 1 | No actors defined or only "the user" with no detail |

### Rule VQ-D04: Interface and Interaction Preferences (Critical)

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | All delivery interfaces checked and described; interaction style identified; accessibility needs stated or confirmed not applicable |
| 4 | Primary delivery interfaces identified and described; interaction style noted; accessibility addressed |
| 3 | At least one delivery interface clearly identified; limited description of interaction style |
| 2 | Interfaces implied but not stated (e.g., "the web app" mentioned elsewhere without being listed here) |
| 1 | Section empty or not completed |

**Note**: This dimension is critical because delivery interface selection drives layer structure (GEN-002), UX phase conditionality, and documentation type classification (DOC-002). A missing or incomplete Section 4 forces the architecture agent to guess the system type, producing unreliable results.

### Rule VQ-D05: Key Capabilities (Critical)

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | 6+ capabilities; each has a descriptive name and explanation of what it enables and why it matters; priorities assigned (MVP / Post-MVP / Future); capabilities are business-level not feature-level |
| 4 | 5+ capabilities with names and descriptions; most have priorities; predominantly business-level |
| 3 | At least 5 capabilities with names and descriptions; priorities may be missing; some may be feature-level |
| 2 | 3–4 capabilities or capabilities described too vaguely to extract domains |
| 1 | Fewer than 3 capabilities or capability list is a feature list ("add/edit/delete" type items) |

### Rule VQ-D06: Information and Concepts

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | 4+ concepts defined; each has description, key attributes, relationships, owner, and lifecycle states |
| 4 | 4+ concepts with description, attributes, and relationships; lifecycle states may be missing for some |
| 3 | At least 3 concepts defined with description and key attributes |
| 2 | 1–2 concepts or concepts described without key attributes |
| 1 | Section empty or only generic terms |

### Rule VQ-D07: Workflows and Journeys (Critical)

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | 3+ workflows; each has actor, goal, trigger, frequency, volume, step-by-step narrative, and variations; covers happy path and at least one error case |
| 4 | 3+ workflows with actor, goal, trigger, and steps; frequency and volume may be missing for some |
| 3 | At least 2 workflows with actor, goal, and step-by-step narrative |
| 2 | 1–2 workflows or workflows described as a list without narrative |
| 1 | No workflows or only a single sentence per workflow |

### Rule VQ-D08: Quality Priorities

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | Priorities ranked in order; non-negotiable floors identified; notes explain key trade-offs |
| 4 | Priorities ranked; some explanation of choices |
| 3 | Priorities listed without ranking, or ranked without explanation |
| 2 | 1–3 priorities mentioned without ranking |
| 1 | Section empty or just "quality is important" |

### Rule VQ-D09: Constraints and Non-Goals

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | Non-goals listed; known constraints listed; integration requirements table complete; data sensitivity and compliance checked; scale and team context filled |
| 4 | Non-goals and constraints present; integration requirements noted; data sensitivity addressed |
| 3 | Non-goals and at least one constraint listed; other sub-sections may be empty |
| 2 | Only one of the two main sub-sections completed |
| 1 | Section empty |

### Rule VQ-D10: Success Metrics

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | Business and technical metrics defined; each has target and measurement method; anti-metrics section includes at least 2 failure indicators |
| 4 | Business and/or technical metrics with targets; measurement methods provided; anti-metrics may be missing |
| 3 | At least 2 measurable metrics defined with targets |
| 2 | Metrics mentioned but not measurable ("the system should be fast") |
| 1 | Section empty or only qualitative statements |

### Rule VQ-D11: System Components Vision (Conditional)

This dimension applies **only when the system has multiple distinct components**. Assess whether Section 5 was correctly handled:

| Score | Criteria |
|---|---|
| 5 | Multi-component system: 2+ components defined with type, audience, design character, principles, success criteria, and unique constraints; single-component system: clearly marked N/A |
| 4 | Multi-component: components defined with most fields; single-component: marked N/A |
| 3 | Multi-component: components listed but design character missing; single-component: marked N/A |
| 2 | Multi-component system but section not filled in |
| 1 | Multi-component system but section is empty or section not present in document |

> **AI Instruction**: If the system appears to have multiple components (multiple interfaces mentioned in Section 4, or capabilities that clearly map to different user-facing surfaces) but Section 5 is empty or marked N/A, flag this as a gap. Do not score it as N/A — score it as 2 and recommend completing it.

