## Gap Severity Classification

### Rule VQ-003: Gap Severity Levels

When identifying gaps, classify each as:

| Severity | Meaning | Example |
|---|---|---|
| **Critical** | The architecture agent cannot safely proceed without this information; will produce incorrect domain structure or wrong layer selection | Missing actors entirely; no delivery interface identified; fewer than 3 capabilities |
| **High** | The architecture agent will make significant assumptions that may need correction in Phase 3 | Workflows described but no actors assigned; capabilities listed but no priorities; integrations not mentioned |
| **Medium** | Architecture can proceed but quality or completeness will be limited | Missing lifecycle states; no success metrics; constraints section sparse |
| **Low** | Nice to have; architecture can proceed confidently | Anti-metrics missing; current solutions section sparse; scale context vague |

---

## Minimum Completion Criteria

### Rule VQ-004: Section Completion Minimums

Before any section scores above 2, it must meet these minimum completion criteria:

| Section | Minimum Completion |
|---|---|
| 1. Problem Statement | At least 3 sentences describing the problem, not just the solution |
| 2. Ideal Future | At least 3 sentences describing concrete outcomes |
| 3. Actors | At least 2 rows in the table with all 5 columns filled |
| 4. Interface Preferences | At least 1 checkbox selected and described |
| 5. Component Visions | Either 2+ components described, or "Single component" clearly stated |
| 6. Key Capabilities | At least 5 rows in the table with name, description, and priority |
| 7. Concepts | At least 3 rows in the table with description and key information |
| 8. Workflows | At least 2 workflow blocks with actor, goal, trigger, and at least 3 steps |
| 9. Quality Priorities | At least 5 priorities in ranked order |
| 10. Constraints | At least 2 non-goals and 2 constraints listed |
| 11. Success Metrics | At least 2 metrics with targets and measurement methods |
| 12. Inspirations | Optional — no minimum required |

